name: Black Farmers Collective / YES Farm
address: 715 Yesler Way, Seattle, WA, USA (This is a general location associated with YES Farm and tours)
category: African-American-owned Educational garden tours in Washington
description: The Black Farmers Collective operates YES Farm, an urban farm in Seattle that offers educational programming on urban farming, race, inclusion, and food access. They focus on creating a Black-led food system and providing community building through growing food. Global Family Travels offers "Learn, Serve & Immerse" tours in partnership with them

name: Nurturing Roots
category: African-American-owned Educational garden tours in Washington
description: Nurturing Roots provides sustainable agriculture awareness and education, teaching people how to grow crops and cultivate food. They offer workshops and educational groups for individuals, schools, and community organizations, focusing on local, national, and worldwide environmental issues. They are listed as a community partner by the Commission on African American Affairs - Washington State
